Identity Recognition Demo.¶

An attempt to recognize a person underneath a face mask. This project is trained on a single team member as if a system is using biometrics for login. However you can modify and play around with the code

This folder contains 2 images that you can use:

  • testImage.jpg #has a mask
  • testImage2.jpg #has no mask

You can modify the filepaths below to change it. This project also assumes that you've uploaded this demo onto the top root level of Google Drive; It's meant to be ran under Colaboratory

Confidence from whole face¶

In [25]:
def recognizeFace():
  weightFile = "/content/drive/MyDrive/IdentityRecognitionDemo/face.weights"
  configFile = "/content/drive/MyDrive/IdentityRecognitionDemo/face.cfg"
  namesFile = "/content/drive/MyDrive/IdentityRecognitionDemo/face.names"

  fileLocation = InputImagePath
  net = cv2.dnn.readNet(weightFile, configFile) #pass in trained model weights and configuration file
  classes = [] #store classes here

  #load object class names
  with open(namesFile, "r") as f:
    classes = f.read().splitlines()

  print(classes) #should only be 1

  #load test image
  img = cv2.imread(fileLocation)
  height, width, _ = img.shape

  #prep image blob
  blob = cv2.dnn.blobFromImage(img, 1/255, (416, 416), (0,0,0), swapRB=True, crop=False) #1/255 is scaling

  '''
  #display blob
  for b in blob:
    for n, img_blob in enumerate(b):
      cv2_imshow(str(n), img_blob)
  '''

  net.setInput(blob) #input blob into network
  output_layers_names = net.getUnconnectedOutLayersNames()
  layerOutputs = net.forward(output_layers_names)

  boxes = []
  confidences = []
  class_ids = []

  for output in layerOutputs:
    for detection in output:
      scores = detection[5:] #starting from the sixth element to the end
      class_id = np.argmax(scores) #extract highest score location
      confidence = scores[class_id]
      
      if confidence > 0.5:
        center_x = int(detection[0]*width)
        center_y = int(detection[1]*height)
        w = int(detection[2]*width)
        h = int(detection[3]*height)

        #upper left corner
        x = int(center_x - w/2)
        y = int(center_y - h/2)

        boxes.append([x, y, w, h])
        confidences.append(float(confidence))
        class_ids.append(class_id)

  indexes = cv2.dnn.NMSBoxes(boxes, confidences, 0.5, 0.4)
  font = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_PLAIN
  colors = np.random.uniform(0, 255, size=(len(boxes), 3))

  if(len(indexes) > 0):
    for i in indexes.flatten():
      x, y, w, h = boxes[i]
      label = str(classes[class_ids[i]])
      confidence = str(round(confidences[i], 2))
      color = colors[i]
      cv2.rectangle(img, (x, y), (x+w, y+h), color, 2) #thickness is 2
      cv2.putText(img, label + " " + confidence, (x, y + 20), font, 2, (255, 0, 0), 2)
    return float(confidence)* 100
  else:
    return 0

Confidence from half face¶

In [22]:
def tophalfconfidence():
  sum = float(0)
  detectionCount = 0

  detector = CustomObjectDetection()
  detector.setModelTypeAsYOLOv3()
  detector.setModelPath("/content/drive/MyDrive/IdentityRecognitionDemo/eyeweight.h5")
  detector.setJsonPath("/content/drive/MyDrive/IdentityRecognitionDemo/eyeconfig.json")
  detector.loadModel()
  detections = detector.detectObjectsFromImage(input_image=InputImagePath, output_image_path="eyedetect.jpg")
  for detection in detections:
      #print(detection["name"], " : ", detection["percentage_probability"], " : ", detection["box_points"])
      sum += detection["percentage_probability"]
      detectionCount +=1

  if(detectionCount == 0):
    return 0
  else:
    return sum/detectionCount
